TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Update Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: UPDATE VRAP.RCNT_DEX_CNTL CNTL SET CNTL.DEX_TXN_STAT_CD = :TU.DEX_TXN_STAT_CD, CNTL.UPDT_TS = :TU.UPDT_TS WHERE CNTL.OBJ_GID = :TU.OBJ_GID AND CNTL.OBJ_TYP_CD=2 and CNTL.DEX_ORIG_ENTY_CD = 1 and CNTL.DEX_DEST_ENTY_CD = 2 AND CNTL.DEX_TXN_STAT_CD=1

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Pre SQL
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
delete from VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG stg where exists ( select hdr.dstr_gid from vrap.rcnt_recn_dstr_hdr hdr where hdr.dstr_stat_cd = 15 and hdr.DSTR_CRTE_TYP_CD in (5,11) and stg.dstr_gid = hdr.dstr_gid
)

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: The session populates RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG for Out Come claims that belong to Distribution headers that are in READY TO TRANSMITT status. When it fails, it sends out a failure email and update RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR status to ERROR. There is a pre session sql on SQ SQ_RCNT_RECN_EXTN_CLM to remove all the records for all distributions that are in READY TO TRANSMIT status.
SESSION.NAME: s_m_CASH_Stg_Outcome_Insert_Txn_Stg

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Email Text
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
The mapping %m ran in the %s session in the %w workflow ran in %d.
ONCALL: This process runs every 30 minutes to process any Outcome Distribution in VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR table with DSTR_STAT_CD = 10 - READY TO TRANSMIT.
The process changes DSTR_STAT_CD to 15 - TRANSMITTING right after it starts and changes it to 99 - ERROR if failed or if any Distribution inludes one or more error claims.
Please research on the cause of the failure. To rerun the workflow, 1. reset DSTR_STAT_CD in table RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR with status of 99 - ERROR and/or 15 - TRANSMITTING (in case it failed to update to ERROR) updated from this run with the latest UPDT_TS, to status of 10 - READY TO TRANSMIT. 2. reset the failed Process Controler entry status to NEW to rerun the process from the top.
Target Table: %t
%l
%r
Session Log is attached %g
